<section sectnbr = "6B">
<servcat sctnbr = "06" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B6206009" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Steering Column Removal and Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B6206001">Steering Wheel and Column Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
For handling of removed air bag (inflator) module, refer to 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70B8200002">Precautions for Handling and Storage of Air Bag System Components</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Failure to follow procedures could result in possible air bag system activation, personal injury or unneeded air bag system repairs.
</ptxt>
</attention1>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Steering column is designed to absorb impact by deforming itself. Be sure to take the following in mind when handling removed steering column.
</ptxt>
</item>
<list2 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Dropping steering column assembly on its end could collapse steering shaft or loosen capsules that maintain original column length.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Leaning steering column assembly on wall or anything other could cause it to bend or be deformed.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list2>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not release tilt and telescopic lever with steering column nuts loosened or steering column removed from vehicle. Doing so may increase operating force for tilt or telescopic motion.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Any of the damage could impair the column’s collapsible arrangement.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Steering column mounting nuts should not be loosened with steering shaft joint upper side bolt tightened as, this could cause damage to shaft joint bearing.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B6206009001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove contact coil assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B6206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For ignition switch model, remove immobilizer control module from manual steering lock. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA316001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove lighting switch and wiper switch.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Lighting switch: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9206014"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Wiper switch: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering column hole cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove knee air bag (Inflator) module. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B8206007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For A/T model with ignition switch, remove key interlock cable. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B5106016"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering joint cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B6206001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering lower shaft. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B6206020"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove instrument cluster panel (1). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect P/S control module connector (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A620016.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "74.313mm" ver = "01" gw = "157" gh = "194"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Detach steering column harness clamps (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect P/S control module connector (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For keyless push start model, disconnect auto steering lock connector (3).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
For ignition switch model, disconnect both key reminder switch connector (4) and ignition switch connector (5).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering column mounting lower and upper nuts (6) and reinforcement nut (7).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<title>
Keyless push start model
</title>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A620017.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "78.458mm" ver = "05" gw = "165" gh = "206"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<title>
Ignition switch model
</title>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A620042.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "78.784mm" ver = "01" gw = "165" gh = "207"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering column.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For RHD M/T model, remove steering column lower bracket bolt (1) (if equipped) from steering column lower bracket, if necessary.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B620004.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "63.912mm" ver = "01" gw = "201" gh = "165"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B6206009002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B6206011">Steering Column Inspection (Tilt Type)</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B6206012">Steering Column Inspection (Tilt and Telescopic Type)</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Be sure to install steering lower shaft after tightening steering column mounting nuts and reinforcement nut. If steering lower shaft is installed before tightening the nuts, steering shaft joint of steering column may be damaged.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check that vehicle’s front wheels are at straight-ahead position.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For RHD M/T model, install steering column lower bracket bolt (1) (if equipped) to steering column lower bracket, if removed.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B620004.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "63.912mm" ver = "01" gw = "201" gh = "165"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering column.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten steering column mounting lower nuts (1) and then tighten steering column mounting upper nuts (2) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install reinforcement nut (3) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
When installing, make sure that clearance “a” between bolt (4) and bracket (5) should be 0 (zero).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After installing tilt steering column, make sure that steering column moves upwards and downwards smoothly and stops when tilt lever is fixed.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T6B002">
<t-part>
Steering column mounting lower nut*
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
14
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.4
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
10.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T6B003">
<t-part>
Steering column mounting upper nut*
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
14
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.4
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
10.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T6B004">
<t-part>
Steering column reinforcement nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
c
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
5.5
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
0.56
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
4.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For keyless push start model, connect steering lock connector (6).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
For ignition switch model, connect both key reminder switch connector (7) and ignition switch connector (8).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect P/S control module connector (9).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Attach steering column harness clamps (10) in place.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<title>
Keyless push start model
</title>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B620001.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "102.936mm" ver = "01" gw = "225" gh = "275"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<title>
Ignition switch model
</title>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B620002.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "103.759mm" ver = "01" gw = "224" gh = "278"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect P/S control module connector.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install instrument cluster panel. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering lower shaft. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B6206020"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering joint cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B6206001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For A/T model with ignition switch, install key interlock cable. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B5106016"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install lighting switch and wiper switch.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Lighting switch: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9206014"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Wiper switch: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For ignition switch model, install immobilizer control module to manual steering lock. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA316001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install contact coil assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B6206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering column hole cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
